<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>General Info and Ettiquette</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
This site handles like most discussion boards.  There are various categories with various forums.  Within each forum topic are a variety of discussion threads.  Discussion threads tend to be about a specific subject while others may be free flowing and ever changing.  When possible it is best to keep the discussion on topic.  Ocassionally people chase rabbits or hijack a thread and the discussion gets off topic.  Occassionally a moderator or an administrator may request that you get back on topic.  That is really out of respect for those who initially began that thread and want to stay on topic. It is also best to keep your thread in the correct forum.<br>
<br>
One thing that is common with most EZBoards is concerning posting information about third parties.  EZBoard wants to avoid legal entanglements with third parties.  That means that we must be careful to not name or post links of certain prop dealers or private collectors unless you are that prop dealer or collector.  There are a number of laws concerning licensing and intellectual property.  As such, EZBoard can revoke our board if they receive complaints or negative communications.  It is best to take specifically named discussions to private email.  Also, please avoid posting prices.  Again this is an EZBoard thing.  It is an inconvinience, but a minor one for what we get from EZBoard.<br>
<br>
Try to be respectful of others.  We all make fun of each other and cut up.  Fun is fun, but try to know or learn when to stop.  Also, I don't care about minor profanity, but try to keep it to a minimum.  EZBoard would like that to be  that way.  We all know when we're crossing the line, so just be aware.  Understand that occassionally a moderator or administrator may edit your post when they feel that something is out of line or out of place.  It's nothing personal, we just want to keep our board.<br>
<br>
A different area of the board will be discussed in the next post. <p>&quot;Mu'Dai Mfg&quot;<br>
