<br>
The main question that many people ask is about getting a personal Icon to appear.  In order to get an Icon, you will need to have an image that is stored somewhere and can be linked to.  Some people have personal web pages or picture hosting accounts that they can keep digital pictures stored on.  Those pictures have URL address telling web browsers where that image is located.  To find out what the URL is of an image, right click on that image and select properties.  There you will see the url of that image.  It will look something like this:  <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.yourdomain.com/image.gif">www.yourdomain.com/image.gif</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
It is the URL of the image you will need to copy.<br>
<br>
Then go to the main page of the Bloodwing Discussion Board and click on &quot;my control center&quot; located in the upper left portion of the page.  This will take you to your control panel.  Then you need to click on &quot;edit profile&quot;.  One of the first entry boxes you will see says &quot;personal photo&quot;.  This is where you will need to put in the URL of the image that you want as your personal Icon.  Be sure to un-check the &quot;private&quot; box so that the Icon will appear.<br>
<br>
In order for your Icon to appear in posts, you may also have to check the &quot;include personal photo&quot; box prior to hitting the &quot;add reply&quot; button.  One other thing to note:  ICONS WILL ONLY APPEAR IN NEW MESSAGES POSTED SINCE CREATING THE ICON.  Unlike the Fan Force board, old messages will not have your new icon.  Instead it will be whatever your old icon was or lack there of. <p>&quot;Mu'Dai Mfg&quot;<br>
